As we know iut has been at lockdown since march 17. Meaning no Bangladeshi student is staying at iut hall since march 17. But we have already paid the hall fee and tuition fee for this semester. We've paid for the hall but due to the situation we are not allowed to stay there. So, we should get a refund of our hall fees from the date of iut going into lockdown to the date of iut reopening. But iut authority is yet give us any formal notice regarding the matter of refund. In the last official notice iut authority mentioned that 150 students can stay in the halls if they wish to. But our classes are still being conducted online. So, why would anyone stay in the halls. We, the students of batch 18 who stay in the halls are deeply concerned about IUT not refunding our hall fee. We have discussed this with our parents and they are concerned too. They are willing to talk with the new VC about this matter. A rough estimate of how much money we should get is given below. 
IUT takes 1500$ for 10 months of hall accommodation from its students who don't have any full or partial scholarship.
That means 150$ per month. 
Since we don't have to pay again before the start of our next education year , we decided to divide the 10 month into half with 5 months for each semester. For the first semester of the year 2020,
we have stayed in hall for 2.5 month(As the winter semester was supposed to end in may) . So we should get back the money for the other 2.5 month of the first semester. So if we put it in terms of numbers
(Considered 10 month cuase iut doesnât allow Bangladeshi students to stay at hall during November December.)
(2.5x150$x84)=31,500 tk
We should get back this amount for the first semester.
The second semester only just started. If we do the entire second semester online we should also get back 5months worth hall fee for the second semester. If we take that into account the amount becomes,
31,500+(5x150$x84)=94,500tk 
(The amount might change if physical classes start before the end of the current semester)
So, 94,500tk is the rough estimated amount we should get back from our hall fees.
We are also thinking about asking for refund of 20% of the tuition fee as the online education in no way is worth 3000$ a year.
Please don't take this as a laughing  matter. This pandemic has put many families in financial crisis. That amount of money is could help a family more than we think.
